Police made arrests during a public auction at the Agriculture Fund building in Pilsen
The anti-corruption police have carried out several arrests at the Agricultural Fund building in recent days.
The detectives married a local media businessman and real estate businessman Luboš G.
It appears that he attempted to manipulate an ongoing public auction for the restitution of the rights in such a way that the auctioned land would be received by a specific interested party.
He had to pay Luboš G. half a million crowns.
"At the moment I can only say that the police are looking for a person for bribery during a public auction and public bidding," Antonie Zelená, the chief prosecutor of Pilsen, told Právo, adding that at the moment it can't disclose more details about the ongoing investigation.
After 24 hours, the police released the 46-year-old businessman.
How he could influence the public auction, given the little official information, can only be speculated.
Lubomíra Černá, a spokeswoman for the Agriculture Fund, responded to Právo’s questions by saying that the police actually carried out the arrest at the Pilsen headquarters and was during a public auction.
“It’s a client, not one of our employees,” he said.
According to Černá, the public auction is called "Call for the submission of proposals for land transfer in accordance with the land law" and is carried out when several stakeholders appear in relation to the offered land.
“These people, during the call, offer a higher value than their restitution, which must be transferred before the value of the land is announced.”
“On the basis of the offers, the order of buyers is determined and then the Agricultural Fund transfers the land to the person who offers the largest offer,” the spokeswoman of the Fund explained.
Luboš G. had information on who was going to be presented to the call and, since he was also an interested party because he acquired various restitution rights, he proposed to the interested parties on the ground that he would not participate in the auction.
For that reason, he was charging a commission.
This would explain that, at the time of the arrest, he had so much money on it.
Luboš G. had special contacts in the Pilsen Fund for a long time.
He appeared in the case of the former head of the PF Václav Sankot, who was accused of dispatching the replacement of land for which a construction decision had already been issued.
For example, Luboš G. has just obtained from the Fund some planned land for the construction of public infrastructure, in particular on the site where a large road to the industrial area of Borská pole should be built.
Afterwards, he exchanged them very beneficially with the magistrate for a house in the historic centre of the city itself with a much higher value.
In this case, the municipality had to intervene because, otherwise, the blocked land would avoid construction.
