The Senator could still face a disciplinary measure from the Senate Ethics Committee.
Ensign lawyers said the Justice Department had “informed us that Senator Ensign is no longer a target of his investigation and that he has no plans to raise charges against him on this subject.”
The Justice Department did not want to comment on the case.
