Called PLM, this powerful computer instrument has been used to design assembly chains of manufacturing plants around the world, power plants, high-precision instruments.
The goal is to reproduce, faithfully simulate the product or process before constructing it in a real way, thus avoiding failures and avoidable costs.
PLM has facilitated the development of Canon cameras, Sukhoi aircraft, or Nissan’s most famous utility cars.
