“Pakistan has had to hire personnel with strict religious beliefs to protect nuclear facilities; given the fall in educational and cultural levels, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recruit people who work on nuclear or missile programs,” Russian Foreign Ministry expert Yuri Korolev said at a meeting with U.S. counterparts.
The most novelty of the documentation filed by Julian Assange’s portal is the increasingly diminishing cooperation between the US and Pakistan on nuclear proliferation issues and the high pace of Pakistan’s production of nuclear weapons.
